cardie, France":"Chaumont, Oise, Picardie, Frankrig","France":"Frankrig","Normandy, France":"Normandie, Frankrig","Paris, Île-de-France, France":"Paris, Île-de-France, Frankrig"},"nl":{"1091–1175":"1091–1175","1105–1175":"1105–1175","1117–1137":"1117–1137","1060–1116":"1060–1116","1063–1120":"1063–1120","1091":"1091","1117":"1117","1116":"1116","1105":"1105","1137":"1137","about 1119":"circa 1119","1120":"1120","about 1137":"circa 1137","1175":"1175","1063":"1063","1060":"1060","Chaumont, Oise, Picardie, France":"Chaumont, Oise, Picardie, Frankrijk","France":"Frankrijk","Normandy, France":"Normandie, Frankrijk","Paris, Île-de-France, France":"Paris, Île-de-France, Frankrijk"},"en":{"1091–1175":"1091–1175","1105–1175":"1105–1175","1117–1137":"1117–1137","1060–1116":"1060–1116","1063–1120":"1063–1120","1091":"1091","1117":"1117","1116":"1116","1105":"1105","1137":"1137","about 1119":"about 1119","1120":"1120","about 1137":"about 1137","1175":"1175","1063":"1063","1060":"1060","Chaumont, Oise, Picardie, France":"Chaumont, Oise, Picardie, France","France":"France","Normandy, France":"Normandy, France","Paris, Île-de-France, France":"Paris, Île-de-France, France","nameMeanings":[{"name":"de","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Chaumont","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Gilles, Raoul, Yvon.  Spanish Alicia, Andres, Arturo, Beatriz, Elia, Jose, Julio, Miguel, Raul.","French: habitational name from any of numerous places called Chaumont ‘bald mountain’ (ultimately from Latin <i>calvus mons</i>), for example in Cher, Orne, Jura, Haute-Savoie.","English (of Norman origin): habitational name from Chaumont in Orne (see 1 above)."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Guillaume","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Germanic.  See  <b>William</b> ."],"variants":[{"name":"William","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Guillaume de Chaumont - Seigneur de Chaumont et de Quitry was born in 1091, in France, his father, Ormond I 'le Vieux' de Chaumont - Seigneur de Chateau de Chaumont, was 31 and his mother, Hadwide de Quitry, was 28. He married Dame Isabelle de France - Dame le Liancourt Saint Pierre about 1119. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1175, in Paris, Île-de-France, France, at the age of 84."},"et":{"1091–1175":"1091–1175","1105–1175":"1105–1175","1117–1137":"1117–1137","1060–1116":"1060–1116","1063–1120":"1063–1120","1091":"1091","1117":"1117","1116":"1116","1105":"1105","1137":"1137","about 1119":"umbes 1119","1120":"1120","about 1137":"umbes 1137","1175":"1175","1063":"1063","1060":"1060","